<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900905-0049</DOCNO><DOCID>900905-0049.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Coal andamp; Allied Industries Ltd.:   After-Tax Operating Profit   For the Fiscal Year Soared</HL><DATE>09/05/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A11</SO><CO>   A.CNA</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)COAL PRODUCERS (COA)DIVIDENDS (DIV)</IN><LP>   Coal andamp; Allied Industries Ltd. of Australia, a coalproducer, reported that operating profit after taxes for theyear ended June 30 soared to 60.3 million Australian dollars(US$49.1 million) from A$2.4 million a year earlier, citingan increase in coal sales, higher selling prices inU.S.-dollar terms and a lower Australian dollar.   Per-share earnings more than doubled to A$1.136 from 47Australian cents. Total operating revenue rose 28% to A$603.9million from A$470.5 million. Saying that increasedefficiency and lower financing costs also boosted returns,Coal andamp; Allied raised the dividend to 60 cents a share from 16cents.</LP><TEXT>   Overall profit after accounting for extraordinary itemsjumped 76% to A$52.2 million from A$29.7 million. In thelatest period, the company had an extraordinary loss of A$8million, related mainly to the closure of an engineeringdivision; year-earlier results included an A$27.4 millionextraordinary gain.</TEXT></DOC>